🎯 30-Second Interview Answer

What is enum?

"enum is a user-defined data type that allows us to define a group of named integer constants. It improves code readability and avoids using hard-coded numeric values."

What is typedef?

"typedef creates an alias for an existing data type. It does not create a new type; it simply gives an existing type another name, making code shorter and easier to read."
